### Dark Rebirth
*1st-level death knight feature*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

Becoming a death knight results in straddling the line between the living and the dead, existing in both worlds and neither.

Every death knight shares a number of physical traits: their eyes glow with a pale blue light that leaks icy mist, their body feels cool to the touch, and their voice gains a deep echo. Their emotions and memories from before they became a death knight are typically dulled. They also gain an eternal hunger for causing suffering and death, an addiction that if not sated regularly will inevitably result in insanity.

___
As a death knight, you gain the following traits: 
- Your creature type changes to undead.
- You don’t need to eat, drink, or breathe.
- You don’t need to sleep, and magic can’t put you to sleep. You can finish a long rest in 4 hours if you spend those hours in an inactive, motionless state, during which you retain consciousness.
- You no longer age and will not die from old age.
- You have advantage on death saving throws.
- At your option, you can also pick from or roll on the Death Knight Quirks table to create a quirk for your character.

