Each knighthood has a list of associated spells. You gain access to these spells at the levels specified in the knighthood description. Once you gain access to an knighthood spell, you always know it and the spell doesn't count against your number of spells known.

If you gain a knighthood spell that doesn't appear on the death knight spell list, the spell is nonetheless a death knight spell for you.

